A North West farmer claims to have seen a meteorite strike Botswana Central South African radio station OFM announced on Sunday that footage had been sent from a farmer in Ottosdal, showing a meteorite that struck Botswana on Saturday night. Members of a neighbourhood watch received reports of a bright light before receiving the CCTV footage from Barend Swanepoel and Wikus van Zyl from a farm near Klerksdorp. READ MORE:Â Mauritius, Botswana and Namibia the safest African countries for women Other South African eyewitnesses reported that they too saw the meteorite strike in what they believed to be Botswana.  Courtesy of OFM